The paper deals with the efficient identification of emerging stories and events from a stream of user-generated content, which involves the maintenance of dense subgraphs under streaming edge weight updates. This problem is relevant to several areas of computer science, including social media analysis (cs.SI), information retrieval (cs.IR), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), stream data processing (cs.SD), and database systems (cs.DB). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
